From: Cash Conway <cashconway@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] winemac.drv: Re-hide cursor when macOS unilaterally shows it

macOS can override [NSCursor hide] when the cursor enters certain
system trigger zones (such as the Dock auto-show region at the bottom
of the screen). When this happens during exclusive fullscreen via
CGDisplayCapture, the system cursor becomes visible even though
Wine's cursorHidden flag is still TRUE.

The driver currently calls [NSCursor hide] exactly once and never
re-asserts the hidden state. This patch adds two mechanisms to
detect and correct desynchronized cursor visibility:

1. Add NSTrackingCursorUpdate to the tracking area options so that
   cursorUpdate: is called whenever macOS changes the cursor. The
   handler calls updateCursor:TRUE to re-assert the correct state.

2. In updateCursor:, when force is TRUE and the cursor should be
   hidden, check CGCursorIsVisible() to detect if macOS has
   unilaterally shown it, and re-hide if needed.

This mirrors the approach used by GLFW to fix the same issue
(glfw/glfw#2656).

Wine-Bug: https://bugs.winehq.org/show_bug.cgi?id=XXXXX
Signed-off-by: Cash Conway <cashconway@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m    | 12 ++++++++++++
 dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_window.m | 10 +++++++++-
 2 files changed, 21 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m b/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m
--- a/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m
+++ b/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_app.m
@@ /* updateCursor: method */
 - (void) updateCursor:(BOOL)force
 {
     if (force || lastTargetWindow)
     {
         if (clientWantsCursorHidden && !cursorHidden)
         {
             [NSCursor hide];
             cursorHidden = TRUE;
         }
+        else if (clientWantsCursorHidden && cursorHidden && force)
+        {
+            /* macOS can unilaterally show the cursor when it enters system
+               trigger zones (e.g. the Dock auto-show region at the bottom
+               of the screen). Detect this desynchronization and re-hide. */
+            if (CGCursorIsVisible())
+            {
+                [NSCursor hide];
+            }
+        }

         if (!cursorIsCurrent)
         {

diff --git a/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_window.m b/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_window.m
--- a/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_window.m
+++ b/dlls/winemac.drv/cocoa_window.m
@@ /* NSTrackingArea creation in createWindowWithFeatures: */
     /* We use tracking areas in addition to setAcceptsMouseMovedEvents:YES
        because they give us mouse moves in the background. */
     trackingArea = [[[NSTrackingArea alloc] initWithRect:[contentView bounds]
                                                  options:(NSTrackingMouseMoved |
                                                           NSTrackingActiveAlways |
+                                                          NSTrackingCursorUpdate |
                                                           NSTrackingInVisibleRect)
                                                    owner:window
                                                 userInfo:nil] autorelease];

@@ /* Add cursorUpdate: handler to WineWindow */
+- (void)cursorUpdate:(NSEvent *)event
+{
+    /* macOS sends cursorUpdate: when the system changes the cursor,
+       for example when the cursor enters a Dock trigger zone. Force
+       a cursor state refresh to re-assert our hidden/custom cursor. */
+    [[WineApplicationController sharedController] updateCursor:TRUE];
+}
